	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary01_0.jpg"/>
				<dateline><placeName key="Annapolis, MD"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"
						>Annapolis, Maryland, Camp Burnside November</placeName> —<date> Friday,
						Thursday 22, 1861</date></dateline>
				<p xml:id="a1"><name type="weather ">This is a bright fair day</name>. We got up
					about seven, <objectName type="food">breakfast</objectName>, company drill,
					dress parade, supper brought &amp; is quickly through &amp; evening. Visited
					over to see our sick — <persName key="Henry Miller"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper100"
						>Henry Miller</persName>, <persName>Hogan</persName> &amp; <persName
						key="James A. Kelley"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper045"
						>Kelly</persName> in the <placeName>hospital</placeName>. Sent them
						<objectName type="food">tea and toast</objectName>. The
						<placeName>hospital</placeName> situation and the
						<placeName>hospital</placeName> arrangements are far from comfortable.
					Besides them lay <persName key="Charles Drainer"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper018"
						>Charles Drainer,</persName> weakened down with a severe hemorrhage, &amp;
					not long for this world. He was with our <orgName>company</orgName> in the three
					months service &amp; was lately in <placeName key="Hagerstown, MD"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl042"
						>Hagerstown.</placeName> He has been discharged in the service, went out
					into <placeName>town</placeName> to inquire for <persName>Mrs.
						Monroe,</persName> but since he has moved away to take charge of
						a<placeName> school</placeName> at <placeName>Frederick.</placeName> His
						<persName> brother Harry </persName>has now charge of the seminary.
						<persName> Col. Hartshorne’s lady</persName> was here this evening. The
						<persName>Col.</persName> returned from <placeName key="Washington, D.C."
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl091"
						>Washington</placeName> this evening.</p>
			</div>
		</body>
